<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-17T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-17T01:00:00-05:00" n="387" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11796: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-17T14:00:00+08:00">February 17, 1932—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 17—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>238. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“February 16, 6 p.m. Today’s press reports state that <persName corresp="#p_HC3">Hsi Chia</persName> from Kirin, and
                                        <persName corresp="#p_CC4">Chang Ching-hui</persName> from
                                    Harbin, arrived at Mukden yesterday and <persName corresp="#p_MC1">Ma Chan-shan</persName> here today. The
                                    long-delayed conference in regard to the denunciations [<hi rend="italic">declaration?</hi>] of the new state is
                                    scheduled to open on the 17th or 18th and one Japanese press
                                    report makes the definite statement that the state will be
                                    declared before February 25th.</p>
                                <p>Apparently this movement is being energetically pushed by
                                    interested parties at this time and judging from appearances
                                    early developments are to be expected.”</p></quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>